                     HARRY SPOONER (23) 



                        PLEADED GUILTY



                     to stealing twelve books and other articles, the property of 



                        Leolyn Hart;



                     also to forging and uttering an authority for the payment of £10 1s. 3d.; 



                     also to forging and uttering a request for the payment of £10 1s. 3d.;



                     also to unlawfully attempting to obtain from the 

                        Army and Navy Co-operative Supply, Limited, £10 1s. 3d., with intent to defraud. 




                        Nine months hard labour. No sentence was passed in connection with the larcenies from Mr. Hart, who wished not to press the charge.—And
